Data
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ ERC165Interface
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when querying IERC165.interfaceId
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should always return true
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when attempting to unregister IERC165.interfaceId
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should still return true
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ RegisteredInterfaces
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when an interface has been registered
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true for that interfaceId
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when multiple interfaces have been registered
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true for each registered interfaceId
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the same interface is registered multiple times
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should still return true (idempotent)
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ UnregisteredInterfaces
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when an interface has never been registered
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return false
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when an interface has been unregistered
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return false
в””в”Ђв”Ђ SpecialInterfaceIds
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when querying 0xffffffff and it has not been registered
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return false per ERC-165
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when querying 0x00000000 and it has not been registered
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return false
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when 0xffffffff has been explicitly registered
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when 0x00000000 has been explicitly registered
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true

Register
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ SingleInterface
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when registering a standard interface (e.g. ERC721)
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should mark that interface as supported
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when registering IERC165.interfaceId
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should remain supported (no regression)
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ MultipleInterfaces
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when registering a list of distinct interfaceIds
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should mark all as supported
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when registering a list containing duplicates
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should still end up with all interfaces supported
в””в”Ђв”Ђ CallerIndependence
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when any caller invokes the library register function
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should update interface support without checking msg.sender

Unregister
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ SingleInterface
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when unregistering a previously registered interface
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should mark that interface as unsupported
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when unregistering an interface twice
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should remain unsupported (idempotent)
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ EffectIsolation
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when unregistering one interface
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should not affect support for other interfaces
в””в”Ђв”Ђ ERC165Sticky
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when attempting to unregister IERC165.interfaceId
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should remain supported

Storage
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Slot
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when reading the ERC165 storage slot
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should equal keccak256("erc165")
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when computing the mapping slot for a registered interfaceId
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should contain 1 at keccak256(abi.encode(interfaceId, slot))
в””в”Ђв”Ђ Consistency
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when comparing supportsInterface to the raw storage value
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the same boolean

IntegrationWithDiamond
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ BaseSetup
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the diamond is deployed with ERC165Facet installed
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should support IERC165.interfaceId via the diamond proxy
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when querying via the diamond before any facet registers extra interfaces
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return false for unregistered interfaceIds
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ FeatureFacets
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when an ERC20 facet has registered its interfaceId
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ the diamond supportsInterface should return true for ERC20
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when an ERC1155 facet has registered its interfaceId
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ the diamond supportsInterface should return true for ERC1155
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when a facet is removed and its interfaceId unregistered
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ the diamond supportsInterface should return false for that interfaceId
в””в”Ђв”Ђ Upgrades
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when upgrading facets that add or remove interfaceIds
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ supportsInterface should reflect the new set of interfaces

Gas
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when calling supportsInterface for IERC165.interfaceId
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should consume less than 30,000 gas
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when calling supportsInterface for a registered interfaceId
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should consume less than 30,000 gas
в””в”Ђв”Ђ when calling supportsInterface for an unregistered interfaceId
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should consume less than 30,000 gas

